# Rangova — Full Admin Panel + Supabase Backend

## Overview

This plan covers:
1. **Supabase** setup — auth, database, storage for all images
2. **Node.js Express API** backend — all CRUD endpoints
3. **React Admin Panel** — complete replacement of the stub `Admin.jsx` with a full-featured admin dashboard
4. **Frontend wired to API** — replace hardcoded data with Supabase/API calls

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Before I can start building**, I need the following from you:
> 1. **Supabase Project URL** — e.g. `https://xyzabc.supabase.co`
> 2. **Supabase Anon/Public Key** — from your Supabase dashboard → Settings → API
> 3. **Admin Username & Password** — what credentials do you want for the admin panel login? (e.g. `admin` / `rangova@2024`)
>
> These will be stored in a `.env` file — **never committed to git**.

> [!WARNING]
> This is a **significant architectural change**. The frontend currently uses hardcoded data in `products.js`. After this change, all data will come from Supabase via a Node.js API. The existing static `PRODUCTS` array will be seeded into the database on first run.

